    "value": [10,   12,   11,   15,   14,   18,   17,   20,   22,   25]

display(df)

```python
import numpy as np
df['score_bin'] = np.where(df['score']<0.4, 'low', np.where(df['score']<0.7, 'mid','high'))
df_bin_kpi  = df.groupby('score_bin').agg(mean_value = ('value', 'mean')).reset_index()
df_bin_kpi['diff'] = df_bin_kpi['mean_value']-df["value"].mean()
better_bins = df_bin_kpi[df_bin_kpi['diff']>0]['score_bin'].to_list()
display(df, df_bin_kpi, better_bins)
```

```python
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
custom_order = ['low','mid','high']
# Convert the column to a categorical type with the custom order
df_bin_kpi['score_bin'] = pd.Categorical(df_bin_kpi['score_bin'], categories=custom_order, ordered=True)

# Sort the dataframe by the now-ordered 'team' column
df_bin_kpi_sorted = df_bin_kpi.sort_values('score_bin')
color = np.where(df_bin_kpi_sorted['diff']>0, 'blue', 'gray')
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(6,4))
ax.bar(df_bin_kpi_sorted['score_bin'], df_bin_kpi_sorted['mean_value'], color = color)
ax.set_title("Mean Value by Score Segment")
ax.set_xlabel("Score Segment")
ax.set_ylabel("Mean Value")
ax.grid(False)
ax.axhline(df["value"].mean(), color = 'gray',linestyle='--',linewidth=2)
```
